ard on someone, you treat them severely or unkindly.\nDon't be so hard on him.", '苛刻的;严厉的;不友善的\n别对他太苛刻了。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nIf you say that something is hard on a person or thing, you mean it affects them in a way that is likely to cause them damage or suffering.\nThe grey light was hard on the eyes...\nThese last four years have been hard on them.', '有害的;不利的\n光线暗淡对眼睛不利。\n过去的这四年里他们吃了不少苦。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nIf you have a hard life or a hard period of time, your life or that period is difficult and unpleasant for you.\nIt had been a hard life for her...\nThose were hard times.', '（生活、一段日子）艰难的，艰苦的\n对她而言，那是一段非常艰苦的生活。\n那些岁月是非常艰难的。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nA hard winter or a hard frost is a very cold one.\n...a prolonged period of hard frost...\nI am expecting a long, hard winter.', '非常寒冷的;凛冽的\n漫长的强霜冻期\n我估计冬天会漫长而寒冷。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nHard colours or sounds are harsh or bright and unpleasant to see or hear.\nThe sea was a hard blue.', '（颜色）刺目的，晃眼的;（声音）刺耳的，难听的\n大海呈一片耀眼的蓝色。'], ['ADJ\nHard evidence or facts are definitely true and do not need to be questioned.\nHe wanted more hard evidence...\nThere are probably fewer hard facts about the life of Henry Purcell than that of any other great composer since the Renaissance.', '（证据、资料）可靠的，确凿的\n他想要更多确凿的证据。\n有关亨利·普赛尔生平的可靠资料可能比任何其他文艺复兴以来的伟大作曲家都要少。'], ['ADJ-GRADED\nHard water contains a lot of calcium compounds that stop soap making bubbles and sometimes appear as a deposit in kettles and baths.', '（水质）硬的（指含钙化合物较多）'], ['ADJ\nHard drugs are very strong illegal drugs such as heroin or cocaine.', '（毒品）毒性强的，烈性的'], ["ADJ\nIn phonetics, a hard sound is one such as 'c' or 'g' as pronounced in the words 'cat' or 'give', and not as in the words 'cinema' or 'general'.", '（语音）发硬音的'], ['PREP-PHRASE\nIf one thing is hard by another, it is very close to it.\nParadise Street was a short, crowded street near the railway station and hard by the factory.', '离…很近的\n天堂街是火车站附近一条拥挤的小街道，离该工厂很近。'], ['PHRASE\nIf you feel hard done by, you feel that you have not been treat